OL,3,C'A disgrace to the uniform': Ex-
OL,4,Cofficer jailed over murder probe calls
OL,6,F"Ultimately it turned into a murder
OL,7,Fenquiry where the son of the household
OL,8,Fyou contacted was a suspect," the
OL,9,Fjudge told Atkinson, highlighting that
OL,10,Fthe pensioner "is the only person in
OL,11,Fthis courtroom" who could shed light
OL,12,Fon the contents of that call.JJudge
OL,13,FLynch added however that Atkinson has
OL,14,Fnever shown any co-operation and "even
OL,15,Fnow will not shed light on the fateful
OL,16,Fphone call".J"The public are entitled
OL,17,Fto expect the highest degree of
OL,18,Fprobity from those entrusted to police
OL,19,Fand enforce the law," the judge told
OL,20,FAtkinson and declared: "You have been
OL,21,Fa disgrace to the uniform."JFollowing
OL,22,Fsentencing, the family of Robert
OL,23,FHamill called for the findings of the
OL,24,Fpublic inquiry into his murder to be
OL,25,Fmade public.JCatch up with the latest
